ered by an indpendant indvidual who would take anyone who signed up on the boards. In this case it seems that the opertunity to get armor is based on a regulation instead of enterpising indvidual raids. The only reason i disagree with this is I think alot more people could get armor and such if you had raid leaders post there raids on a board and make it free for all to sign up, then of course select who yout think would benifit the best from the raid. <br>
<br>
         Im simply making an observation and contributing to what i have experienced on my server. For instance i got a full suite of Wizard fear armor in less then 4 weeks. Because i could go on raids between 3-4 times even 7 times a week if i had time. Anyone have some thought into this. I mean really in my humble oponion i think that raids should be for everyone to have a shot, and focus more on the fun of it, instead of rugulating it to a specific rotation of guilds, that seems more like a communist way of leading. Of course when you raid things like naggy or vox or Cazic Thule of course there will be a council for the loot pre-determined prior, but as far as armor goes, seems a bit slow to me. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
