<br>
And yep we just follow the rules hehe, KGC is the rotation board. (I think in all honesty there is no true enforcement body on the server, its just the greater will that keeps people in line) <br>
<br>
Some guilds hand out armor based on senority or officership or even lvl, CoG is simply a way for everyone not in an uber to still get there. Everyone gets a roll and no one is left out. If I cared about armor that badly I wouldnt have only 3 pieces and been planes capable for over 10 months now, I would have switched servers. Then again I probably would have lvled more if I didn't need a white dragon scale so badly for my GL's epic.<br>
<br>
There have been discussions on KGC about switching to FFA. The overwhelming majority said &quot;nope&quot; (there was only 1 guild that advocated for a FFA system) It's a lovely idea and I'm sure on other servers it might work, but we love our rotation. It keeps things civil, fair and fun. Be welcome to post it though, I'd be interested to see Vyktor's thoughts on it.<br>
<br>
*drops 2 copper in the &quot;my opinion&quot; jar*<br>
